# Risk Management Plan

| Risk | Possible problem | How the group will manage it |
|------|------------------|------------------------------|
| Tool is too difficult | Prototype may not be completed | Use a simpler backup tool such as Canva, PowerPoint, Scratch, Twine, or Google Forms |
| Only one person does the work | Weak collaboration evidence | Every member must have assigned tasks and GitHub commits |
| AI overuse | Students may not understand the work | Record AI use and edit/check all AI output |
| Poor time management | Presentation may be rushed | Set short milestones and check GitHub weekly |

---

# Summary

Our group created a structured prototype development plan to ensure the cyber-safety mini game is completed on time. Each member has assigned responsibilities, milestones are clearly defined, and risks are managed with backup solutions and regular progress tracking.
